-- ============================================================================
-- NELA v0.4 — Quicksort Algorithm
-- LLM-OPTIMIZED SINGLE-SECTION FILE
-- ============================================================================
--
-- SECTION INDEX FOR LLM NAVIGATION (auto-maintained):
--   SECTION_QUICKSORT    [ 17- 24]      qs
--
-- ARCHITECTURE:
--   Single recursive sorting function: qs
--   Pattern: divide (by pivot), conquer (sort sub-lists), combine (concatenate)
--   No imperative loops; pure functional composition
--   Runs in Python test suite as reference implementation
--
-- COORDINATES: N/A (sorting algorithm; not game logic)
--
-- ── @SECTION_QUICKSORT [17-24] ────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Functions: qs
-- Purpose: Sort integer list using quicksort algorithm
-- Called_by: test suite (runtime.py)
-- Key_vars: [lst, h, t]
-- Details:
--   - Partition: h (pivot) vs. elements <= h (left), > h (right)
--   - Recursively sort left and right sublists
--   - Concatenate: left ++ [pivot] ++ right
--   - Base case: empty list returns empty

def qs lst =
  match lst
  | []    = []
  | h::t  = qs [x <- t | x <= h] ++ [h] ++ qs [x <- t | x > h]
